# Plan: Add `mistral-instruct-v3` Specialized Chat Template Handler

## Context

`common/chat.cpp` contains a two-tier system for chat templates:
1. **Jinja rendering** – the Jinja template (embedded in the model file) produces the prompt string.
2. **PEG-parser dispatch** – `common_chat_try_specialized_template()` inspects the raw Jinja source for unique markers and routes matching templates to hand-written specialized handlers that know how to parse the *response* (content, tool calls, reasoning tokens). Templates that match no specialized handler fall through to the differential autoparser.

The **Mistral Instruct v0.3** format (e.g., `mistralai-Mistral-Nemo-Instruct-2407.jinja`) currently falls through to the autoparser. The task is to add a dedicated specialized handler for it:

- **Prompt format**: `[INST]{user}[/INST]` per user turn; system message prepended to first user turn as `[INST]{system}\n\n{user}[/INST]`; assistant turns end with `</s>` (eos token).
- **Tool call format**: `[TOOL_CALLS][{"name": "...", "arguments": {...}, "id": "..."}]</s>` (array-wrapped JSON, distinct from Ministral-3's `[TOOL_CALLS]name[ARGS]json` format).
- **Distinguishing marker**: has `[INST]` but **no** `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]` (Ministral-3 always has `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]`).

## Constraint

Only **add** new code. Do **not** modify any existing handler functions, the detection blocks for other handlers, or any header file (`chat.h`, `chat-peg-parser.h`, `llama-chat.h`, etc.).

## Critical Files

| File | Role |
|---|---|
| `common/chat.cpp` | **Only file to edit.** Add handler function + detection block. |
| `common/chat-peg-parser.h` | Read-only reference – `common_chat_peg_builder::standard_json_tools()` (line 108) handles JSON-array tool call parsing. |
| `models/templates/mistralai-Mistral-Nemo-Instruct-2407.jinja` | Reference Jinja source – the canonical Mistral v3 template; has `[INST]`, `[AVAILABLE_TOOLS]`, `[TOOL_CALLS]`, but **no** `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]`. |
| `models/templates/mistralai-Ministral-3-14B-Reasoning-2512.jinja` | Reference – has `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]`; caught by the Ministral-3 handler. Won't conflict. |

## Existing Pattern to Mirror

All specialized handlers in `common/chat.cpp` follow this skeleton (see `common_chat_params_init_gigachat_v3`, lines 1446–1517, for the simplest reference):

```cpp
static common_chat_params common_chat_params_init_<name>(
        const common_chat_template & tmpl,
        const autoparser::generation_params & inputs) {
    common_chat_params data;

    data.prompt           = common_chat_template_direct_apply_impl(tmpl, inputs);
    data.format           = COMMON_CHAT_FORMAT_PEG_NATIVE;
    data.preserved_tokens = { /* special tokens used in the format */ };

    auto has_tools       = inputs.tools.is_array() && !inputs.tools.empty();
    auto include_grammar = has_tools && inputs.tool_choice != COMMON_CHAT_TOOL_CHOICE_NONE;

    auto parser = build_chat_peg_parser([&](common_chat_peg_builder & p) {
        // return root PEG rule
    });
    data.parser = parser.save();

    if (include_grammar) {
        data.grammar_lazy = inputs.tool_choice == COMMON_CHAT_TOOL_CHOICE_AUTO;
        data.grammar      = build_grammar(...);
        data.grammar_triggers = { ... };
    }
    return data;
}
```

## Step-by-Step Implementation

### Step 1 – Add the handler function

**Location**: `common/chat.cpp`, immediately before `namespace workaround` (after the closing `}` of `common_chat_params_init_gigachat_v3`, around line 1517).

```cpp
// Mistral Instruct v0.3 format:
// - User turns: [INST]{content}[/INST]
// - System message prepended to first user turn: [INST]{system}\n\n{user}[/INST]
// - Assistant turns end with </s> (eos_token)
// - Tool calls (Mistral-Nemo / v3): [TOOL_CALLS][{"name":"...","arguments":{...},"id":"..."}]
// Distinct from Ministral 3: no [SYSTEM_PROMPT] in the Jinja source.
static common_chat_params common_chat_params_init_mistral_instruct_v3(
        const common_chat_template &          tmpl,
        const autoparser::generation_params & inputs) {
    common_chat_params data;

    data.prompt           = common_chat_template_direct_apply_impl(tmpl, inputs);
    data.format           = COMMON_CHAT_FORMAT_PEG_NATIVE;
    data.preserved_tokens = {
        "[INST]",
        "[/INST]",
        "[TOOL_CALLS]",
    };

    auto has_tools       = inputs.tools.is_array() && !inputs.tools.empty();
    auto include_grammar = has_tools && inputs.tool_choice != COMMON_CHAT_TOOL_CHOICE_NONE;

    auto parser = build_chat_peg_parser([&](common_chat_peg_builder & p) {
        auto generation_prompt = p.literal(inputs.generation_prompt);

        if (!has_tools || inputs.tool_choice == COMMON_CHAT_TOOL_CHOICE_NONE) {
            include_grammar = false;
            return generation_prompt + p.content(p.rest());
        }

        // Mistral v3 tool calls are a JSON array prefixed by [TOOL_CALLS]:
        //   [TOOL_CALLS][{"name":"fn","arguments":{...},"id":"abc123def"}]
        const bool force_tools = inputs.tool_choice == COMMON_CHAT_TOOL_CHOICE_REQUIRED;
        auto tool_parser = p.standard_json_tools(
            /* section_start    = */ "[TOOL_CALLS]",
            /* section_end      = */ "",
            inputs.tools,
            inputs.parallel_tool_calls,
            force_tools,
            /* name_key         = */ "name",
            /* args_key         = */ "arguments",
            /* array_wrapped    = */ true,
            /* function_is_key  = */ false,
            /* call_id_key      = */ "id");

        return generation_prompt +
            (force_tools ? p.eps() : p.content(p.until("[TOOL_CALLS]"))) +
            tool_parser +
            p.end();
    });

    data.parser = parser.save();

    if (include_grammar) {
        data.grammar_lazy = inputs.tool_choice == COMMON_CHAT_TOOL_CHOICE_AUTO;

        data.grammar = build_grammar([&](const common_grammar_builder & builder) {
            foreach_function(inputs.tools, [&](const json & tool) {
                const auto & function = tool.at("function");
                auto         schema   = function.at("parameters");
                builder.resolve_refs(schema);
            });
            parser.build_grammar(builder, data.grammar_lazy);
        });

        data.grammar_triggers = {
            { COMMON_GRAMMAR_TRIGGER_TYPE_WORD, "[TOOL_CALLS]" }
        };
    }

    return data;
}
```

### Step 2 – Register the detection block

**Location**: `common/chat.cpp`, inside `common_chat_try_specialized_template()` (starts at line 1634), immediately **after** the closing brace of the existing Ministral-3 block (after line 1644), before the GPT-OSS block.

```cpp
    // Mistral Instruct v3 - uses [INST]/[/INST] user turns with system prepended to first user
    // turn and </s> after assistant turns; distinct from Ministral 3 by absence of [SYSTEM_PROMPT]
    if (src.find("[INST]") != std::string::npos &&
        src.find("[SYSTEM_PROMPT]") == std::string::npos) {
        LOG_DBG("Using specialized template: mistral-instruct-v3\n");
        return common_chat_params_init_mistral_instruct_v3(tmpl, params);
    }
```

## Why These Choices

| Decision | Rationale |
|---|---|
| `standard_json_tools(array_wrapped=true, name="name", args="arguments", call_id="id")` | Exactly matches the `[TOOL_CALLS][{"name":...,"arguments":...,"id":...}]` format in `mistralai-Mistral-Nemo-Instruct-2407.jinja`. |
| Detection: `[INST]` present + `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]` absent | Task requirement; Ministral-3 check (which requires `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]`) comes first in the function, so there is no ordering conflict. |
| No reasoning/thinking support | Mistral Instruct v0.3 has no thinking tokens; `supports_thinking` left at its default (`false`). |
| Detection inserted after Ministral-3 block | Keeps Mistral-family handlers together; ordering is safe because the two conditions are mutually exclusive. |
| `p.end()` at the end of the tool-call branch | Matches the autoparser generator pattern for JSON native tool calls. |

## Verification

1. **Build** – `cmake --build build` should succeed with no new warnings.
2. **Template smoke test** – run `./build/bin/test-chat-template models/templates/mistralai-Mistral-Nemo-Instruct-2407.jinja` and verify the new log line `"Using specialized template: mistral-instruct-v3"` appears.
3. **With tools** – run `./build/bin/test-chat-template --with-tools models/templates/mistralai-Mistral-Nemo-Instruct-2407.jinja` and confirm the grammar/PEG parser is generated without errors.
4. **Ministral-3 unaffected** – run `./build/bin/test-chat-template models/templates/mistralai-Ministral-3-14B-Reasoning-2512.jinja` and confirm the log still reads `"Using specialized template: Ministral/Magistral Large 3"`.
5. **Existing test suite** – `cd build && ctest -R test-chat` to confirm no regressions.

